---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<Layout
  title="Research Opportunities"
  description="Join the CAL DMRadio dark matter experiment. Open positions for graduate students, postdocs, and undergraduates."
>

  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Join the Collaboration</span>
      <h1>Research Opportunities</h1>
      <p class="desc">
        We are actively recruiting motivated researchers at all levels. Work at the
        frontier of quantum sensing, dark matter physics, and RF engineering.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why join -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="two-col-60">
        <div>
          <span class="section-label">Why DMRadio</span>
          <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">What You'll Work On</h2>
          <p style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
            [Replace with a compelling description of the research environment: cutting-edge quantum
            sensing technology, direct relevance to a major unsolved problem in physics, collaborative
            team, access to Berkeley resources, etc.]
          </p>
          <p style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
            DMRadio researchers gain hands-on experience with dilution refrigerators, SQUID amplifiers,
            superconducting circuits, RF electronics, data analysis, and statistical methods for
            rare-event searches.
          </p>
          <p>
            [Add information about Berkeley Physics, research culture, and any fellowships or funding
            available to new group members.]
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;">
          <div class="info-box">
            <h4 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Skills you'll develop</h4>
            <ul style="list-style:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem;">
              {['Cryogenic systems & dilution refrigerators', 'SQUID amplifiers & quantum sensing', 'Superconducting resonators & RF design', 'Data analysis & statistical inference', 'Dark matter theory & phenomenology', 'Scientific writing & presentations'].map(s => (
                <li style="display:flex;gap:0.5rem;align-items:flex-start;font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--gray-600);">
                  <span style="color:var(--gold);font-weight:700;flex-shrink:0;">&mdash;</span> {s}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider">

  <!-- Open roles -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">Open Positions</span>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Current Openings</h2>

      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1.5rem;">

        <!-- Postdoc -->
        <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--blue);">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">
            <div>
              <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.25rem;">Postdoctoral Researcher</h3>
              <span class="tag tag-blue">Open</span>
              <span class="tag" style="margin-left:0.25rem;">Full-time</span>
            </div>
            <a href="mailto:pi@berkeley.edu" class="btn btn-primary" style="font-size:0.875rem;">Apply via email</a>
          </div>
          <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
            [Describe the postdoc role: key responsibilities (e.g., lead detector commissioning,
            SQUID characterization, data analysis), required qualifications (PhD in experimental
            physics or related field), desired experience (cryogenics, RF, quantum sensing), and
            expected start date.]
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--gray-500);">
            [Add salary range, benefits, and duration of appointment. Berkeley postdoc salary is
            set by NIH guidelines. Appointment is typically 2 years with possibility of renewal.]
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Grad student -->
        <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--blue);">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">
            <div>
              <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.25rem;">PhD Graduate Student</h3>
              <span class="tag tag-blue">Open</span>
              <span class="tag" style="margin-left:0.25rem;">PhD Program</span>
            </div>
            <a href="https://physics.berkeley.edu/graduate/prospective-students" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-secondary" style="font-size:0.875rem;">Apply to Berkeley Physics</a>
          </div>
          <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
            [Describe the graduate student role: thesis topics available (resonator design,
            SQUID readout, analysis pipeline, new detector concepts), whether you are accepting
            students for the current application cycle, and what background (undergrad physics,
            electronics, programming) is helpful.]
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--gray-500);">
            Graduate students apply through the UC Berkeley Physics PhD program. Prospective students
            are encouraged to email the PI directly with a brief description of their interests.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Undergrad -->
        <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--gold);">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">
            <div>
              <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.25rem;">Undergraduate Researcher</h3>
              <span class="tag tag-gold">Open (semester basis)</span>
            </div>
            <a href="mailto:pi@berkeley.edu" class="btn btn-secondary" style="font-size:0.875rem;">Send an email</a>
          </div>
          <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
            [Describe undergraduate opportunities: hardware testing, software/DAQ contributions,
            data analysis projects. Mention URAP, SURF, or other Berkeley programs that support
            undergraduate research. Typical time commitment: 10&ndash;15 hrs/week.]
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--gray-500);">
            We welcome undergrads with enthusiasm for physics, some programming experience, and
            availability of at least one semester. Credit and/or stipend may be available.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider">

  <!-- How to apply -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div>
          <span class="section-label">How to Apply</span>
          <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Getting in Touch</h2>
          <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
            For postdoc and undergraduate positions, send an email to the PI at
            <a href="mailto:pi@berkeley.edu" style="color:var(--blue);text-decoration:underline;">pi@berkeley.edu</a>
            with the subject line <strong>"DMRadio [Role] Application"</strong> and include:
          </p>
          <ol style="padding-left:1.5rem;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
            <li style="font-size:0.9375rem;color:var(--gray-600);">A brief statement of your research interests and why DMRadio excites you</li>
            <li style="font-size:0.9375rem;color:var(--gray-600);">Your CV or resume</li>
            <li style="font-size:0.9375rem;color:var(--gray-600);">Unofficial transcripts (undergrads) or publication list (postdocs)</li>
            <li style="font-size:0.9375rem;color:var(--gray-600);">Names of 2&ndash;3 references (postdocs)</li>
          </ol>
          <p>
            Graduate students should apply through the
            <a href="https://physics.berkeley.edu/graduate/prospective-students" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--blue);text-decoration:underline;">Berkeley Physics PhD program</a>
            and are welcome to contact the PI to express interest.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="highlight-box">
            <h4 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;color:var(--blue);">Contact</h4>
            <p style="font-size:0.9375rem;margin-bottom:0.5rem;"><strong style="color:var(--gray-900);">Professor Name</strong></p>
            <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--gray-500);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Professor of Physics, UC Berkeley</p>
            <a href="mailto:pi@berkeley.edu" style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--blue);">pi@berkeley.edu</a>
            <hr style="margin:1rem 0;border:none;border-top:1px solid var(--gray-200);">
            <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--gray-600);">
              [Department &amp; office location]<br>
              University of California, Berkeley<br>
              Berkeley, CA 94720
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
